Alone, the 'this' keyword refers to the window object.

Ex:
console.log(this)

OUTPUT:
[object Window] {
  addEventListener: function addEventListener() { [native code] },
  alert: function alert() { [native code] },
  atob: function atob() { [native code] },
  blur: function blur() { [native code] },
...
...
...


Window object is basically the entire browser.
The information of this entire tab is contained within this window object.
